BLUETONGUE, BOVINE - LUXEMBOURG: OIE
*************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: 1 Dec 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: OIE Disease Alert [edited]
<http://www.oie.int/Messages/061201LUX.htm>

Bluetongue in Luxembourg (Disease never reported before in Luxembourg)
-----------------------------------------------
Translation of information received on 30 Nov 2006 from Dr. Arthur
Besch, Director of the Veterinary Services Department, Ministry of
Agriculture, Viticulture and Rural Development, Luxembourg:
Report date: 30 Nov 2006
Reason for immediate notification: 1st occurrence of a listed disease
or infection in a country or zone/compartment.
Identification of agent: bluetongue virus serotype 8.
Date of 1st confirmation of the event: 29 Nov 2006.
Date of start of the event: 24 Nov 2006.
Clinical disease: no.
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory.
Location of the outbreak: Hupperdange, Heinerscheid commune (Clervaux canton).
Number of animals in the outbreak: one case and 80 susceptible animals.
Description of affected population: cattle returning from grazing
ranges in Belgium.
Laboratory where diagnostic tests were performed: Veterinary and
Agrochemical Research Centre (CERVA) (regional reference laboratory).
Diagnostic test used: RT-PCR.
Source of outbreak or origin of infection: introduction of new
animals; contact with infected animal(s) at grazing/watering; vectors.
Control measures undertaken: control of arthropods; movement control
inside the country; screening; zoning.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[An excellent map showing the geographical relationship between this
outbreak and other BT8 outbreaks in Europe can be seen at
<http://www.defra.gov.uk/animalh/diseases/notifiable/pdf/bt-europemap.pdf>.
Also, many thanks to Hubert Deluyker of the European Food Safety
Agency for directing us to an excellent website containing periodic
bulletins including outbreak summaries, analysis, an epidemic curve
and very informative cumulative outbreak and kernel smoothed surface
density maps; see
<http://www.efsa.europa.eu/en/in_focus/bluetongue/outbreak_overview.html>.
- Mod.PC]
